    <notesToEditors>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>The <strong><a id="OWAd3c56eaa-5e72-87ea-1ca4-fb481d58b878" rel="noopener" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1c8646206413459ba51fe1df6b9aaed2}" target="_blank" title="Outdoor Learning Hub at QMU" data-auth="NotApplicable" data-loopstyle="linkonly" data-linkindex="1"><span class="marktrk0fgos9" data-markjs="true" data-ogac="" data-ogab="" data-ogsc="" data-ogsb="">Outdoor Learning Hub and Discovery Trail</span></a></strong><a id="OWA7404d53f-31b0-740f-7dcb-2f23a932e2fb" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/study-here/learning-facilities/outdoor-learning-hub-at-qmu/" target="_blank" data-auth="NotApplicable" data-loopstyle="linkonly" data-linkindex="2">,</a> also includes:  </p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Maggie's Wood: </strong>the tiny wood behind the bike racks in University Square is available for activities, <span class="markxywzl9paw" data-markjs="true" data-ogac="" data-ogab="" data-ogsc="" data-ogsb="">learning and teaching.  This space will become more accessible for all as we develop path access.  </span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><a id="OWA24587a87-4009-650e-ccb5-5bfa85563a48" rel="noopener" href="/{localLink:umb://document/6437feaba2ba4831af670669653ef550}" target="_blank" title="2022.02.25 - Planting of ‘Wee Forest’ begins at Queen Margaret University" data-auth="NotApplicable" data-loopstyle="linkonly" data-linkindex="3">The Wee Forest:</a></strong> planted in 2022 surrounding The Howff. The Wee Forest consists of 600 Scottish trees that are part of a Global Citizen Science project.  </p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Online materials: </strong>including information films, resources and links can be found at <a id="OWAd301f305-ab01-799f-1722-91bd16ef0bf6" rel="noopener" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1c8646206413459ba51fe1df6b9aaed2}" target="_blank" title="Outdoor Learning Hub at QMU" data-auth="NotApplicable" data-loopstyle="linkonly" data-linkindex="4">QMU’s <span class="marktrk0fgos9" data-markjs="true" data-ogac="" data-ogab="" data-ogsc="" data-ogsb="">Outdoor Learning Hub</span></a>. Currently in the final stages of development.   </p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Interested in getting involved in QMU’s <span class="marktrk0fgos9" data-markjs="true" data-ogac="" data-ogab="" data-ogsc="" data-ogsb="">outdoor learning work? Contact lecturer Patrick Boxall in QMU’s Education Team: </span><a id="OWAa36fb8d4-4835-bfb3-efa1-70f951678cc3" href="mailto:Epboxall@qmu.ac.uk" title="Email Patrick Boxall" data-loopstyle="linkonly" data-linkindex="5">pboxall@qmu.ac.uk</a>. </p>
<p><em>For further media information contact Lynne Russell, Communications Manager, Queen Margaret University, Edinburgh, EH21 8JL, M: 07711 011239, E: </em><em><a id="OWA524fd7b3-af7c-50c1-eedc-778b232d4834" href="mailto:lrussell@qmu.ac.uk" title="Email Lynne Russell" data-loopstyle="linkonly" data-linkindex="6">lrussell@qmu.ac.uk</a></em><em>, (please copy to E: </em><em><a id="OWA196444fb-2bcd-5a78-1c33-f72589d6c260" href="mailto:pressoffice@qmu.ac.uk" title="Email Press Office at QMU" data-loopstyle="linkonly" data-linkindex="7">pressoffice@qmu.ac.uk</a></em><em>). </em> </p>]]></Value>
